\par\par \b \uc2 Scrutinizing the candidate  \b0\par\par\uc2 Few political parties have shown much enthusiasm in announcing their Jakarta governor candidates, even though election day is drawing near.  \par \uc2 738 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 March 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 Discussions about the candidacy have made headlines, but the parties seem reluctant to name their choices for replacing Governor Sutiyoso, who will step down in October after 10 years in power.  \par \par \uc2 Only the Islam-based Prosperous Justice Party has announced a candidate, Adang Darajatun, former National Police deputy chief.  \par \par \uc2 There are other promising potential candidates who are yet to receive official support from a party, including Sarwono Kusumaatmadja, former environment minister and former secretary general of the Golkar Party during the Soeharto era, Rano Karno, a film star, economist Faizal Basri, former minister Agum Gumelar, former Strategic Reserve Command chief Lt. Gen. (ret) Bibit Waluyo and retired police general Nur Faizi.  \par \par \uc2 It is unclear why the parties are yet to announce firm candidates. It was recently reported that the Star Reform Party (PBR) had confirmed its nominations of Agum and current Deputy Governor Fauzi Bowo. But the official announcement will only be made after the party's central board of executives has approved the nomination.  \par \par \uc2 Voting day is currently scheduled to fall in August. Parties have until the end of May to name their candidates. Eligible candidates will be announced at the end of June, and the campaign period is slated from July 13 to the end of the month.  \par \par \uc2 With Adang the only confirmed candidate, voters are having a difficult time scrutinizing the field.  \par \par \uc2 Given the tight schedule, it is imperative the parties announce their candidates so as to give voters time to examine them and learn about them. In a direct election, the voters need to know a lot about the candidates before casting their lot.  \par \par \uc2 A big question is why doesn't the Democratic Party, which has 16 seats in the City Council, announce its candidate as early as possible?  \par \par \uc2 The Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle, which has 11 seats, was reportedly to have agreed to establish a coalition with six other parties: Golkar, the United Development Party, the National Mandate Party, the National Awakening Party and the PBR, as well as the Democratic Party. But the plan now looks likely to fail, as the PBR has nominated Agum and Fauzi and Golkar is likely to also nominate Fauzi as its candidate.  \par \par \uc2 While things are \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , voters do not have an idea of the best candidate. Their only reference could be the results of a study conducted by the Institute of Research, Education and Information on Social and \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs and the Indonesian Survey Institute, which say that Agum and Fauzi are the most favored candidates and Rano Karno the most popular deputy candidate. The survey, which involved 440 respondents, found that Agum's popularity was due to his clean track record. Adang's appeal is said to be growing, however, following his frequent appearances on television and in the media as the head of the Association of Indonesian Blood Donors.  \par \par \uc2 If all of the candidates, except Adang, are confirmed in May, the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  will have just two months to examine them. The \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  should receive more information on them as the first direct election is a milestone and will be a model for the next elections and a move toward a more democratic Jakarta. The capital city has for decades accepted President-appointed governors.  \par \par \uc2 As the democracy movement has grown, direction gubernatorial elections hold the promise of electing an ideal leader.  \par \par \uc2 National-level elections have made it clear that candidates are not as good as they look during the campaign period. Thus, it is a must that the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  gets to know political candidates as early as possible, in order to have more time in which to scrutinize them.  \par \par \uc2 Prior to Sutiyoso's first election as governor, Jakartans had little information on him except that he was a former Jakarta military commander. Many residents who were aware that he was not their ideal leader could do nothing but accept his election.  \par \par \uc2 Jakartans long for a governor with vision who is capable of addressing the city's myriad problems.  \par \par \uc2 But with gubernatorial aspirants shy to sell themselves to political parties, and with parties remaining undecided over their candidates, it will become more and more difficult for voters to make the best choice. If this situation is being orchestrated by the political parties themselves, all they are doing is planting a time bomb.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020070303e3330000j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
