\par\par \b \uc2 Condition critical:  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  reforms cannot wait   \b0\par\par\uc2 Vincent Lingga , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 661 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 March 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Reform is never easy when it requires changes to an entrenched \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  system. That is why broad-based reforms often require a crisis or perception of crisis, or at least a sense of chronic deterioration. It was \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis that brought down Soeharto in May 1998 and ushered in the reform era.   \par \par \uc2 And we are once again mired in a critical condition now, despite the macroeconomic stability the government often boasts of.   \par \par \uc2 With unemployment and underemployment estimated at some 40 million and the number people living on less than US$2/day exceeding 100 million, our situation is clearly critical.   \par \par \uc2 But both the government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  have yet to demonstrate a sense of crisis in accelerating the reform measures sorely needed to reinvigorate investment, generate jobs and lift people out of poverty.   \par \par \uc2 We had expected good sense to prevail in the end, but the Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono administration, currently in the middle of its term, has yet to demonstrate a feeling of urgency toward \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms in priority areas.   \par \par \uc2 The experiences of other countries that have been successful in pushing through broad reforms shows that the timing of reform depends on political leadership - the leadership to make it clear that there is a crisis.   \par \par \uc2 The government moved decisively in October, 2005 to reform the energy sector by slashing fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  through a 125 percent increase in fuel prices after the rupiah had come under fierce attacks by speculators.   \par \par \uc2 This move immediately gained rewards from the market in the form of confidence in the rupiah and has substantially increased the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  capacity.   \par \par \uc2 But it is rather mind-boggling to notice how apparently ignorant the government and politicians at the House have been for not being able to identify the crisis conditions that should have forced them to accelerate reforms.   \par \par \uc2 Look how deliberations of the \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , labor, investment and mining bills, already several years behind schedule, have been protracted, stuck on issues that are not very important to stimulating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  efficiency. Likewise, reform in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration, including local governments and state companies , has been quite slow.   \par \par \uc2 The challenges lie on two fronts. While the pace of reform \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been much slower than expected, the implementation of reform measures is even more disappointing. The cascading impact of this delay is a disappointingly slow recovery in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and private investments.   \par \par \uc2 The government was commended for the comprehensive reform packages in infrastructure and investment it launched in the first quarter of last year. However, their implementation has dragged.   \par \par \uc2 The crash program to construct 10,000 megawatts in additional power generation capacity seems to have crashed amid bickering about tender procedures and allegations of corruption.   \par \par \uc2 The negative impact of the slow pace of reform is already being felt in the quality of growth as the number of jobs created by one unit of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is now much smaller than before 2000.   \par \par \uc2 The steady rise in unit labor costs in excess of productivity and rigid labor regulations have prompted new investors to economize on labor by avoiding labor-intensive businesses.   \par \par \uc2 Banks, whose function is supposed to center on lending, prefer plowing their funds into debt instruments that have nothing to do with financing real \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities.   \par \par \uc2 Inefficiency and rampant corruption within the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector, notably in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 , customs and business licensing, remain the most serious obstacles to new investment and the main source of business risk.   \par \par \uc2 We often fail to realize that besides legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which makes it extremely difficult to do a reasonable risk calculation, corruption is also a source of unpredictability because any deal could be undone by someone bribing someone in the government.   \par \par \uc2 President Yudhoyono received a strong political mandate in 2004 from disillusioned people who want things to change, but he seems unable to show the leadership necessary to translate this broad dissatisfaction into concrete action and move things in the direction the people want.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020070312e33c00004\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 BI: RI's  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  Overshadowed by  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 376 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 March 2007\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) reminds that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2007 will be overshadowed by risks and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , although \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities are estimated to grow well.   \par \par \uc2 Indonesian 2006 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  report launched by BI yesterday analyzes the risk emerges because of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown and below-expectation investment climate.   \par \par \uc2 The global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown is triggered by, among others, the US \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown.   \par \par \uc2 In addition, the prices of some Indonesian major export commodities are worried to hit below the target since there are disruptions in some rice-producing countries.   \par \par \uc2 "The condition will trigger inflation pressure on domestic volatile food group," read BI report.   \par \par \uc2 If problems related with investment climate improvement in 2007 have yet been solved, BI worries the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth this year will be below expectation and that the inflation rate will increase.   \par \par \uc2 Bi Governor Burhanuddin Abdullah reminded that the yet completed Capital Investment and \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  Laws were factors curbing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth this year.   \par \par \uc2 High-quality investments, he continued, were needed to accelerate the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 He explained that conducive investment climate and high-quality investments were also reflected in the healthy industrial relations between employers and labors.   \par \par \uc2 "Even if the Bills are passed into Laws this year, investments will only start coming next year," he added on the sidelines of the launching of Indonesian 2006 \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Report yesterday.   \par \par \uc2 According to him, this year was a crucial time to maintain optimism for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and to improve the people's welfare.   \par \par \uc2 Inflation Under Control   \par \par \uc2 In the report BI forecasts that the inflation in 2007 will be under control between 6.0% and 6.1%.   \par \par \uc2 The rise in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities this year is estimated not to affect prices in general since implementations of some policies to improve investment climate-improving are expected to make balance between rising demands and supply. As a result, there won't be significant pressures on core inflation.   \par \par \uc2 "The low pressures on core inflation will be supported by the stable rupiah exchange rate against the US dollar in 2007."   \par \par \uc2 In addition, inflation pressures on administered commodities (commodities whose prices regulated by the government] are predicted to be low as the government has no plan to apply fuel prices or electricity \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  hikes. (Bisnis/dle/faa)   \par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020070315e33f00004\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Banking Placement in SBI Understandable: BI Governor   \b0\par\par\uc2 449 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 March 2007\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is of the opinion that it is normal that banking sector has placed the excess of their fund at \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's promissory notes (SBI) amid the high banking liquidity and the slow intermediation process.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's Governor Burhanuddin Abdullah said SBI is an instrument of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to carry out monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . BI has been using the instrument to control the balance of monetary system.   \par \par \uc2 "It is better if the excess of liquidity is placed in SBI than if it goes to anywhere," he said in the sideline of SOE Executive Breakfast Meeting yesterday.   \par \par \uc2 He said other country also has the mechanism to absorb the excess of banking liquidity.   \par \par \uc2 When asked about the criticism of the vice president Jusuf Kalla that placement in SBI is just a kind of robbery he said, "You'd better the vice president."   \par \par \uc2 He said banking placement in SBI is due to the difficulties in implementing intermediary role due to the asymmetric information between bank and industrial sector.   \par \par \uc2 He said banking sector is still traumatic on bad loans as the banking fund has been dominated by the short term one. "It was also due to the micro-structural risk on the rigidity of the offering."   \par \par \uc2 It can be seen, he said, from the undisbursed loan that has increased from IDR143 trillion in January 2006 to IDR179 trillion in January 2007.   \par \par \uc2 The Treasury Director of Bank Lippo Gottfried Tampubolon said the vice president and Kadin should not blame banks for placing the money at SBI.   \par \par \uc2 "We are not stupid. It is better for us to provide some credit than placing the money at SBI. Interest rate of credit is 4 percentage points higher than that of SBI."   \par \par \uc2 The Chairman of Perbanas Sigit Pramono said banking sector has the optimum role to play its intermediary role.   \par \par \uc2 He said that the trust of the trust of the people has been high so that the third party's fund at banking sector has been increasing every year. At the end of 2006 the total credit was IDR792 trillion, representing 20.2% growth per annum in the last fives years.   \par \par \uc2 But he admitted that such growth has not been sufficient to drive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . "Let's find out the way out. We want to increase the loan, but we can not walk alone."   \par \par \uc2 Sigit hopes the government will help by settling the problem on license, on legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , on labor, on regional autonomy - the issues outside the control of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Bank Bukopin's Director Tri Joko Prihanto said the criticism of vice president may drive banking sector to increase the credit this year. (Bisnis/faa/m04)   \par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020070329e33t0000g\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
