\par\par \b \uc2 Beach resort starts to breathe again   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Ciamis   \par \uc2 477 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 July 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Along the popular beach resort of Pangandaran, hotels and tourism businesses have begun to show signs of life.   \par \par \uc2 Many have taken the initiative to rebuild their damaged premises following the July 17 tsunami last year, which destroyed the resort area. Others, however, have not been able to follow suit.   \par \par \uc2 Instead, they have placed "for sale" signs on their plots -- \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  the once-busy tourist area will be able to bounce back.   \par \par \uc2 The tsunami damaged more than 60 hotels at the beach resort in Ciamis regency, West Java, and swept away 1,419 kiosks along beaches in six districts.   \par \par \uc2 Local tourist operators, whose businesses rely on tourism to Pangandaran Beach, have complained about the slow pace of reconstruction.   \par \par \uc2 Thijs de Fretes, a member of the Indonesian Tourist Guides Association in West Java, said recovery efforts at popular beaches in Ciamis should be sped up to restore tourism.   \par \par \uc2 "Tourism helps the local \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and residents who live along the coast," he said.   \par \par \uc2 He said Pangandaran Beach has a strong appeal to tourists, just like Kuta Beach in Bali.   \par \par \uc2 "Restoring infrastructure as well as repairing and adding tourist facilities, such as restaurants or discotheques, might enliven the nightlife here ... make this beach resort become a destination for middle to upper-class tourists."   \par \par \uc2 This year's school holiday, which ended Sunday, helped filled rooms, but it was not enough to help residents get back on their feet.   \par \par \uc2 Apart from fishing, tourism is the main \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  wheel in the regency, contributing around Rp 4 billion (US$444,444) in annual revenue, or a quarter of the regency's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The regency collects income from ticket sales at the 22 tourist sites along Pangandaran Beach; popular for its beautiful sunsets and sunrises.   \par \par \uc2 The administration also collects revenue from fish auctions, hotels and restaurants and through land \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Head of the Ciamis Tourism Office's program supervision division, Apip Winayadi, said the administration lowered its target for tourism revenue to Rp 1.2 billion in 2006 following the tsunami, but a figure of only Rp 750 million was achieved.   \par \par \uc2 Weak tourist numbers saw the regency lower the revenue target to Rp 200 million for 2007.   \par \par \uc2 "We hope 750,000 tourists will visit this year, but only 10 percent of this target has been reached so far," Apip said.   \par \par \uc2 The decline in tourism prompted the State Ministry for Culture and Tourism to work with the province and the regency administrations to boost tourism and lure more visitors by holding a tourism promotional event called Pangandaran Smiling.   \par \par \uc2 The event, which was kicked off by a kite festival on July 7, includes musical performances by popular bands like /rif and Naif, and swimming and surfing contests.   \par \par \uc2 A prayer ritual will also be held to observe the one-year anniversary of the disaster. The event ends July 18.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020070717e37h00008\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
