\par\par \b \uc2 Pump priming  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 The 12 percent increase to Rp 836.4 trillion (US$90 billion) in total government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono proposed for pump priming during \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year 2008 seems ambitious.   \par \uc2 665 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 August 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Bureaucratic inertia has made \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  disbursements painfully slow and we don't see any indication yet of any greater urgency on the part of the government to improve its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  management capability.   \par \par \uc2 The 20 percent rise in civil servant and military pay, which will increase total personnel \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 29 percent to Rp 130 trillion, will help strengthen consumers' purchasing power; but this is far from enough to achieve the 2008 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target of 6.8 percent, up from the 6.3 percent estimated for this year.   \par \par \uc2 The government envisions an almost 50 percent increase in capital expenditures to Rp 101.5 trillion. This is the right kind of \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  that could become a major driver of growth, especially because the bulk of this investment will be spent on basic physical infrastructure such as roads, seaports and airports, and on the development of soft infrastructure such as education and health services.   \par \par \uc2 But we are apprehensive this \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  allocation can be realized according to schedule. For \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  2007, for example, only around 23 percent of the investment \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  had been spent as of last month. \b \highlight22\uc2 Spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the procurement of goods has run a bit faster, but even this reached just 27.5 percent of the budgeted sum.   \par \par \uc2 Hence, there is an uphill battle for the government to improve its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  management to provide the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  much needed to maintain the momentum of growth.   \par \par \uc2 The government should also force local administrations to expedite their \b \highlight22\uc2 budget spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and whenever necessary slap penalties on those administrations that prefer parking their investment budgets in bank deposits or \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  commercial papers.   \par \par \uc2 The government will increase the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  by 21 percent to Rp 75 trillion or 1.7 percent of gross domestic product, but this \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be funded mostly by borrowing from the domestic markets (bonds totaling Rp 91.6 trillion). Official capital accounts will continue to post a net resource outflow amounting to the equivalent of Rp 16.7 trillion, up from Rp 12.6 trillion this year.   \par \par \uc2 This huge borrowing need makes it even more imperative for the government to improve its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  management in a bid to reduce its sovereign risks. Without improvement in sovereign risks, investors will demand high yields on government bonds, thereby increasing the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden.   \par \par \uc2 The government should nevertheless be commended for its transparency in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal, with regards to the risks that may affect its assumptions for key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators used for the 2008 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates.   \par \par \uc2 These estimates are \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 6.8 percent, 6 percent inflation, Rp 9,100 average rupiah exchange rate, 7.5 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  benchmark interest rate and $60/barrel average oil price.   \par \par \uc2 President Yudhoyono elaborated in his state of the union address the likely risks, contingent liabilities and other factors that might influence the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates and consequently the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance next year.   \par \par \uc2 A \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , however well planned, is not self-contained, is not operating in a vacuum, but will be adversely affected by external factors and other converging \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , entrenched patterns of expenditures, inflation and structural imbalances between expectations and resources. The full disclosure of the risks will help improve government credibility in the financial market.   \par \par \uc2 As it happens, the global financial condition now is quite fragile due to the devastating impact of the crisis in the high-risk property loan market in the U.S.   \par \par \uc2 It is helpful though that the government debt ratio to gross domestic product will further decrease next year to 33 percent from less than 40 percent now, as a result of government efforts to cut new foreign borrowing and accelerate old debt amortization (repayment).   \par \par \uc2 All in all, the key to realize the pump priming badly needed to bolster \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is significant improvement in the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  management capacity.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020070820e38k0000m\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 PP on Batam, Bintan, and Karimum Free Trade Zones Issued   \b0\par\par\uc2 344 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 August 2007\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BIS