\par\par \b \uc2 Taxpayers not filing returns   \b0\par\par\uc2 731 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 October 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The latest data on individual income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payers, as revealed by \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  Director General Darmin Nasution last week, was not only shockingly small, but also strikingly contrary to what had been reported by his predecessors.   \par \par \uc2 We assumed, based on the official reports of his predecessor Hadi Purnomo, that Darmin now manages at least 10 million registered individual income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payers, of which almost seven million were netted under a massive campaign in 2005.   \par \par \uc2 However, Darmin put the number of registered income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payers last week at a mere four million. Even more disappointing is only 33 percent or 1.32 million of them filed their annual \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns -- the other 2.68 million were classified as non-filers.   \par \par \uc2 Purnomo, instead of waiting for people to voluntarily register themselves as income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payers, conducted a massive, property-based taxpayer registration in 2005 by sending taxpayer registration numbers to people residing in middle and high-income housing complexes in Jakarta and its surrounding suburbs.   \par \par \uc2 There is nothing wrong with these \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 -collection initiatives because people will hardly voluntarily register themselves as income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payers. The \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office could register as many new taxpayers as it likes and put them in their data base.   \par \par \uc2 But what is then the meaning of such an effort without vigorous collection efforts and strong law enforcement? The taxpayer data would be meaningless. It would fail to broaden the taxpayer base if law enforcement remains quite lax and the institutional capacity of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration is not improved.   \par \par \uc2 It was even quite a painful surprise to learn from Darmin's disclosures that five years ago, the number of taxpayers who regularly filed their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns was still as large as 35 percent of the total registered taxpayers.   \par \par \uc2 What happened to the seven million new taxpayers registered in November, 2005 through their property and car ownership and credit cards? Why had they not filed annual \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns.   \par \par \uc2 Even assuming about 50 percent of the new taxpayer registration numbers recorded in 2005 might have been mistakenly issued to ineligible people -- those who already have taxpayer registration numbers, or the ones whose income is still below the taxable income level -- the number of income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns filers should have still reached at least five million.   \par \par \uc2 Darmin suspected one of the reasons behind the high number of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  non-filers was taxpayers' utter disillusionment with \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials, who unfortunately are still perceived to be among the most corrupt civil servants in the country.   \par \par \uc2 He said his officials would not immediately take repressive measures against the non-filers but would first conduct a persuasion campaign and look into their real \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition to ascertain what was the real factor behind their hesitation to file their annual \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns.   \par \par \uc2 Certainly, newly-registered taxpayers have still to be encouraged to voluntarily comply with their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  obligations by regularly filing their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns. Taxpayers should be educated to understand that filing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns is not a complex process nor a costly exercise. They should be adequately briefed that filing annual \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns should not require the payment of any amount of income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  if their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  self-assessment concludes they have not any \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to the state. Still, they have to file the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns.   \par \par \uc2 There should have been many things extremely wrong with our \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law enforcement if today, five years after the massive reform of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration, only 1.32 million taxpayers have regularly filed their annual \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns and only about four million individual income-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payers have been recorded in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate general's data bank   \par \par \uc2 True, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  compliance based on the willingness of taxpayers to pay \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also influenced by their perception of the integrity of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officers and the government's credibility with regard to governance practices in general. Taxpayers may be discouraged to file \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns if they face \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  about legal \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  matters, or they notice the incidence of corruption within the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration remains extraordinarily high.   \par \par \uc2 However, voluntary \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  compliance also will increase if the cost of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  evasion and non-filing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  returns is very high. More people will fulfill their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  obligations if they know the chance of being caught by \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials and auditors is high. But this environment requires a strong law-enforcement system and a higher \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administrative capacity to collect \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and audit taxpayers.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071002e3a20000m\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
