\par\par \b \uc2 Dispute within government   \b0\par\par\uc2 694 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 October 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Late last month, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono intervened in a dispute between the Supreme Audit Agency and the Supreme Court over the latter's refusal to be audited.   \par \par \uc2 Earlier in the same month, the President was also forced to set up an inter-ministerial team to investigate illegal logging in Riau allegedly connected to several major companies.   \par \par \uc2 The team, which was headed by Coordinating Minister for Political, Legal and Security Affairs Widodo A.S, was formed after the National Police and the forestry minister failed to settle their squabble over the matter.   \par \par \uc2 The team is yet to submit its recommendations to the President, leaving dozens of companies in the area mired in legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Another spat now seems to be unfolding between the Finance Ministry and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the disclosure of what the Supreme Audit Agency described as questionable or dubious state financial accounts opened at state banks by officials.   \par \par \uc2 Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati, in a concerted effort to follow up the auditor's findings, sent an official letter to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's board of governors in August asking for their permission to investigate the questionable accounts.   \par \par \uc2 But more than five weeks later, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  is yet to responded to the finance minister's letter, saying it is yet to complete an internal investigation into the matter.   \par \par \uc2 What a mess cooperation and coordination within the government seems to be in.   \par \par \uc2 Doesn't the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  realize the urgency of verifying the accounts to improve \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  finance management and accountability?   \par \par \uc2 Banking Law No.10/1998 protects the secrecy of bank accounts and the identity of account holders. It also only allows the opening of bank accounts by third parties with prior approval from \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The banking secrecy clause is necessary to encourage people to put their savings in banks.   \par \par \uc2 According to the law, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  can only disclose bank account details in relation to \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  audits or investigations, criminal trials, the settlement of government debts or at the request of certified heirs to accounts.   \par \par \uc2 However, we find it hard to understand why the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has taken such a long time to respond to Sri Mulyani's official request. This, we think, has nothing to do with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's status as a politically independent institution.   \par \par \uc2 True, the banking law does not specifically mention "dubious or questionable accounts" as a factor that can be used to justify \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's approval for the disclosure of bank account details.   \par \par \uc2 But what the finance minister has been endeavoring to do is act on the Supreme Audit Agency's findings regarding almost 495 bank accounts holding a total of Rp 1.5 trillion (US$162 million) in state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds within the Finance Ministry.   \par \par \uc2 The problem, as the auditors found, is that the identities of the account holders and their purposes for opening the accounts are not clear.   \par \par \uc2 As the sole official in charge of managing state finances and the treasury, the minister of finance should be able to verify accounts containing state/government money, as well as accounts opened to hold state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds allocated to various directorates or agencies within the finance ministry.   \par \par \uc2 Such verification is becoming more urgent and imperative. As the Supreme Audit Agency's findings have shown, state financial accounts are often opened without any legal connection to the management of finances.   \par \par \uc2 State auditors once uncovered bank accounts containing more than Rp 2 trillion ($215 million) in state funds that had been dormant for more than two years. Audits also uncovered the equivalent of billions of dollars in state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds, which instead of being disbursed for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  pump priming, were deposited in bank accounts in the names of officials (who certainly enjoyed benefits such as interest).   \par \par \uc2 We find it even more flabbergasting that the state financial accounts which Sri Mulyani had failed to verify until Tuesday were kept at state banks.   \par \par \uc2 President Yudhoyono may have to intervene yet again -- this time to mediate in this spat between the finance minister and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 But if that was the case, the President would most likely have to extinguish even more fires within the government.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071004e3a40000k\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
