\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Central bank \highlight\uc2  keeps key rate unchanged   \b0\par\par\uc2 Urip Hudiono , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 568 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 October 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has held its benchmark interest rate unchanged once again at 8.25 percent, citing rising inflationary expectations ahead and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the global financial markets.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said it believed the current rate was high enough to keep inflation in check within its 5 to 7 percent estimate for the year, while still being low enough to spur growth in the third quarter and beyond at 6.2 percent on lower borrowing costs and higher \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "This decision is intended to consolidate the credibility we have gained so far in maintaining macroeconomic stability so as to support \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  expansion," BI Senior Deputy Governor Miranda S. Goeltom said after Monday's monthly \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  meeting of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's Board of Governors.   \par \par \uc2 This marks the third consecutive time since July, when inflation first picked up this year, that BI has held its rate steady. Before that, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , starting May last year, had trimmed the rate by 450 basis points from 12.75 percent.   \par \par \uc2 BI said that the upward trend affecting both headline and core inflation had continued during the third quarter, with the figures for September being 6.95 percent and 6.03 percent year-on-year, respectively, due to the Ramadhan fasting month and upcoming Idul Fitri holidays. As a result, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would have to particularly "monitor the situation" in relation to its rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 BI also referred to the lingering effects of the U.S. subprime mortgage crisis, which had caused increased capital outflows from the local financial markets, pushing down the rupiah.   \par \par \uc2 "Looking ahead, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding the adjustment of the global financial markets to the subprime mortgage crisis means that we have to continue to be consistent with our prudent monetary policies," Miranda said.   \par \par \uc2 The problems on the global markets appear to have subsided for now -- with capital flowing in and the rupiah strengthening once again. If this were to continue, along with easing inflation, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  says it continues to see room for further rate cuts ahead.   \par \par \uc2 "The BI rate at 8.25 percent will be enough to stimulate growth ahead, as it still leaves room for the banks to lower their own lending rates," Miranda said.   \par \par \uc2 Miranda said that BI expected inflation to ease to between 4 and 6 percent next year, while growth was expected to be "the same or better" than the third quarter's expected 6.2 percent.   \par \par \uc2 BI's decision to hold the rate steady Monday had been widely expected by analysts.   \par \par \uc2 Economist Ryan Kiryanto of  \uc2 Bank Negara Indonesia\uc2  said BI had thoroughly assessed the situation, and the current rate level was sufficient to anticipate a possible weakening of the rupiah due to higher corporate demand for dollars ahead for debt repayments.   \par \par \uc2 "And if global rates continue to ease, then BI can also cut rates again, by November at the latest, to 8 percent by December," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Local markets were also unaffected by BI's decision to keep its rate on hold, having already factored it in, and instead rallied on the back of global sentiment and the prospects of strong third-quarter corporate performances.   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Stock Exchange Composite Index was up 23.12 points to 2,523.70, while the rupiah was slightly stronger by 0.1 percent at Rp 9,075 against the U.S. dollar.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071009e3a90000z\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
