\par\par \b \uc2 The contingency fund   \b0\par\par\uc2 718 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 October 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The 2008 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  that was approved by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  last week is not substantially different from the \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan proposed by President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono on Aug. 16, except for the special allocation of Rp 7 trillion (US$750 million) as a contingency fund.   \par \par \uc2 Both the administration and the House agreed such a contingency fund is necessary as the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is highly vulnerable to changes in the basic assumptions of oil prices and average oil production.   \par \par \uc2 The government has assumed average international oil prices at $60/barrel for 2008 and average daily crude oil production at 1.03 million barrels. But these assumptions could substantially change since oil prices have generally exceeded $75 over the past few months. Even during the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, domestic fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will most likely be much larger than the Rp 56.36 trillion allocated in the 2007 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  because during the first nine months the average oil price exceeded $65/barrel, compared to $60 used as the base price to determine the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Yet more worrisome is that the average daily oil output estimated for the whole of next year may not materialize due to technical difficulties in the start-up of the Cepu oil field in East Java. Preparations for production developments in the field, which is operated by  \uc2 ExxonMobil\uc2 , seem to have been hindered by problems in land acquisition.   \par \par \uc2 If the Cepu oil field does not come onstream next year as scheduled -- which seems highly probable -- Indonesia's daily oil production will remain at 950,000 barrels and more oil will have to be imported to meet domestic needs.   \par \par \uc2 The contingency fund is necessary since a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  system, however well planned, is not self-contained and will be adversely affected by external factors and other multiple, converging \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as well as structural imbalances between expectations and resources.   \par \par \uc2 The financial markets should welcome the government's transparency with regards to the risks of larger-than-estimated expenditures and the appropriation of the contingency fund. Investors will feel more comfortable as they can rest assured that there are unlikely to be many painful surprises ahead.   \par \par \uc2 Such a market perception is positive for reducing the government's sovereign risks and consequently its borrowing costs, because the bulk of its Rp 73.3 trillion \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  next year will be financed with bonds. Without significant improvement in sovereign risks, investors will demand high yields on government bonds.   \par \par \uc2 The House did not change the assumptions used by the government for the 2008 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates: \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 6.8 percent, 6 percent inflation, Rp 9,100 average rupiah exchange rate, 7.5 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  benchmark interest rate and $60/barrel average oil price.   \par \par \uc2 It is also encouraging to note that the House has not pushed ahead with its demand to sharply increase dividend payments from state companies to Rp 31.5 trillion, or almost 50 percent of the projected total net income of all state enterprises. Such a large dividend payout would adversely affect the growth prospects of state companies, and that would not bode well for the overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because many state firms operate in basic infrastructure and upstream manufacturing industries which supply basic materials to downstream factories.   \par \par \uc2 The House and the government finally agreed on a total dividend payout of Rp 26 trillion or 38 percent of the total net profits expected by state companies next year.   \par \par \uc2 The main challenge for the 2008 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is designed to provide \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  pump priming with Rp 103.5 trillion in capital expenditures and Rp 52.4 trillion in goods and service procurements, remains the acutely inadequate \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  management capability both at the central government and regional administrations.   \par \par \uc2 For the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, for example, only 40 percent of capital expenditures had been spent in the first nine months (as of this month) due to bureaucratic inertia and arduous tendering or procurement procedures.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  investment planned for next year is precisely the right kind of \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to drive growth, especially because the bulk of the investment will be spent on basic physical infrastructure such as roads, seaports and airports, and on education and health services.   \par \par \uc2 But these investment commitments will mean nothing if most of them remain unspent and are instead invested in \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's debt papers.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071018e3ai0000s\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Index Declines by 54 Points on Worry for Soaring Inflation   \b0\par\par\uc2 422 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 October 2007\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The Composite Stock Price Index (IHSG) on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (BEJ) again fell yesterday in the wake of worry that the inflation would increase following the soaring international crude oil price to US$90 per barrel.   \par \par \uc2 The index was only able to increase to its new high of 2,641.59 on the first post-Idul Ftiri holiday trading day on Wednesday. Two days later, the index declined to 74.46 points and yesterday was closed at 2,563.75.   \par \par \uc2 The index decline yesterday, touted as the largest in the past two months, was also triggered by negative sentiments in the regional and global markets.   \par \par \uc2 Head of Research at Credit Suisse Mirza Adityaswara revealed the soaring oil price to its record high triggered worry that the inflation would increase.   \par \par \uc2 "The soaring oil price can boost inflation when the industrial oil prices are raised in the next few months," he said as quoted by Bloomberg yesterday.   \par \par \uc2 Dwi Setiawan, an analyst at Valbury Asia Securities Krishna, expressed the same worry, saying the threat of inflation would entice the monetary hawk to boost its rate.   \par \par \uc2 "There has been \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  whether the Federal Reserve will again cut its rate. Market confidence is being undermined. The inflation threat and the impact of the soaring oil price will spread globally," he told.   \par \par \uc2 Corporate Fundamentals   \par \par \uc2 Krishna doubted the soaring oil price would boost the prices of energy stocks as the former would affect the fundamental performances of companies, including undermining corporate profits and macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. "If macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions are not good, no stocks can be considered attractive."   \par \par \uc2 Recently, some energy stocks keep booking profits following the soaring oil price. Five energy stocks making the most significant contribution to the index this week are Bumi Resources, Tambang Batu Bara Bukit Asam,  \uc2 Energi Mega Persada\uc2 ,  \uc2 Aneka Tambang\uc2 , and Timah.   \par \par \uc2 On the other hand, worries over global and domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  have put pressures on the prices of banking stocks in the past two days. As a result, the stock prices of  \uc2 Bank Rakyat Indonesia\uc2 ,  \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , Bank Central Asia,  \uc2 Bank Negara Indonesia\uc2 , Bank Danamon, and Panin Bank dropped.   \par \par \uc2 In the meantime, banking stocks trigger stock index declines in Europe and Asia following the statement made by Bank of Japan Governor Toshihiko Fukui saying the US sub-prime mortgage crisis had increased \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the financial market. In Asia, most of the indices fell, save Hang Seng that slightly rose by 0.57% to 29,465. (Bisnis/pul)   \par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020071020e3ak00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
