\par\par \b \uc2 RI GOVERNOR CITED AS ONE OF WORLD'S BEST STATE BANKERS   \b0\par\par\uc2 662 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 October 2007\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 Asia Pulse Pty Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.   \par \par \uc2 Washington, D.C., Oct 22 (ANTARA): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) Governor Burhanuddin Abdullah was declared one of the world's five best state bankers in 2007 by Global Finance magazine for his success in leading Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , particularly in maintaining macro \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability in 2005.   \par \par \uc2 The Best Central Banker Award was bestowed on Burhanudddn by an executive of Global Fianance, a US-based international \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  magazine, at the National Press Club here Monday in the presence of bankers from across the world.   \par \par \uc2 The four other awardees were \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governors Zeti Akhtar Aziz (Malaysia), Armando M Tetangco, Jr (the Philippines), Fai-Nan Peng (Taiwan) and Israeli \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's Deputy Governor Zvika Eckstein.   \par \par \uc2 Burhanuddin said the award was actually earned by the members of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's board of governors, staff and about 6,000 employees.   \par \par \uc2 "I only worked along with them to do what had to be done," he said after receiving the award.   \par \par \uc2 Global Finance magazine had observed that Indonesia had managed to maintain macro \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability throughout the year 2005.   \par \par \uc2 The fact that the oil price at that time was high had made the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden so heavy and caused high inflation, and thus \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  tried to maintain stability gradually between 2005 and 2006, he said.   \par \par \uc2 In 2005, the interest rate in Indonesia reached about 7.4 percent while the fuel oil price which the government increased by 126 percent on October 1, 2005 caused inflation to shoot up from 8 percent to 17 percent.   \par \par \uc2 When the inflation rate reached 17 percent, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  gradually increased the interest rate up to 12.75 percent.   \par \par \uc2 "With the inflation rate reaching 17 percent and the interest rate at 12.5 percent, our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was actually still on the negative interest rate. However, the people saw that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had taken the right measures at the right time so that they did not care too much about the negative interest rate," he said.   \par \par \uc2 In addition, Indonesia also received other awards from Global Finance, namely, in the categories of Best Sub Custodian Banks ( \uc2 HSBC\uc2 ), Best Trade Finance Providers (Bank Danamon Indonesia) and Best Domestic Banks (Bank Danamon).   \par \par \uc2 The Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor admitted 2008 would be a hard year for efforts to lower the interest rate -- till the middle of 2007 it had reached 8.25 percent.   \par \par \uc2 Based on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's calculations, he said, in 2008 the inflation rate would be high due to different factors in the world including the increase in oil prices and commodities -- like wheat, rice and sugar -- besides global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems because of high \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  following the subprime mortgage crisis.   \par \par \uc2 The subprime mortgage crisie is an issue related to the fall in the rate of housing bonds in the US two months ago which had caused big losses to bond holders, mostly big financial institutions in America, Europe and Asia, and this had affected the world stock market.   \par \par \uc2 However, Burhanuddin said, the increase in the world oil price would give advantages in Indonesia, namely, that the prices of oil palm and rubber would rise. The increase was expected to have a good impact on Indpnesia's balance of payments.   \par \par \uc2 "We have to reach an inflation rate of 5 percent in 2008 although \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's staff have predicted the inflation rate will reach about 6.2 percent," he said.   \par \par \uc2 He said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would take standard measures to reach the inflation rate.   \par \par \uc2 "Firstly, we will see global, national and regional developments gradually and accurately from the viewpoint of commodity prices and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  perspectives," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Secondly, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would thoroughly observe the measures taken by domestic banks, he said.   \par \par \uc2 "Our banks have become very good now. They have distributed high amounts of credit and this year, I think, the amount of credit to be distributed is to reach 22 percent. It will be about the same amount next year," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020071024e3an0000i\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Gov't Anticipates  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  Slowdown   \b0\par\par\uc2 714 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 October 2007\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The government promises anticipative measures to deal with global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in the wake of the soaring crude oil price and the wider effect of the sub-prime mortgage crisis in the US.   \par \par \uc2 President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono explained the government had anticipated the possibility of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown by preparing some options and policies.   \par \par \uc2 "The IMF report is a yellow light for us to prepare anticipative measures and prudent management to prevent the soaring oil price from hampering the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," the President stated when giving his opening speech at the 22nd Trade Expo Indonesia in Jakarta yesterday.   \par \par \uc2 Report by IMF revealed that the world's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would grow by 5.2% in 2007 and by 4.8% next year. IMF also viewed the sub-prime mortgage crisis would affect the risk rate and create global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the future years.   \par \par \uc2 Such condition had made the US revise its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth projection from 2.8% to 2.2%.   \par \par \uc2 Presiden Yudhoyono exposed that the declines of global supply and demand would make tighter competitions for export market share and flow of investments.   \par \par \uc2 Corrections to the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he continued, were triggered among others by the soaring crude oil price, which could affect Indonesia's balance of payment that still provides fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 To win the competition in the tight export market, the President hoped the Indonesian businesses could produce high-quality commodities sold for affordable prices.   \par \par \uc2 On the same occasion, Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Boediono reminded the government needed to stay alerted for the world's potential \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown. The government, he added, had the right policies and only needed to improve the implementations of the policies.   \par \par \uc2 "We should stay alerted. What we need to do is to improve the implementations of the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , monetary policies, and investment climate improvement policies. Te prices of some of our export products are good and our State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is solid."   \par \par \uc2 Still bright   \par \par \uc2 Minister of Trade Mari Elka Pangestu also expressed optimism toward the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook. According to her, the outlook was still bright in the wake of rising demands from non-traditional markets-outside the US, Japan, and the European Union-that would not be affected by the risk of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown.   \par \par \uc2 She cited that the economies in the Middle East would grow stronger on the soaring crude oil price and so would some Asian countries, such as China, South Korea, Taiwan, and Asean member countries.   \par \par \uc2 Mari continued that the measures to anticipate global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown would be decided at a coordinating meeting on \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The government's efforts to help alleviate the burden of the businesses following the soaring oil price could be seen in the national energy blueprint. "We will give more detailed explanation in some other times."   \par \par \uc2 One \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that had been implemented, according to Mari, was the provision of duty facility for the industries that were willing to convert their energy needs.   \par \par \uc2 Nevertheless, she stated that the businesses had to find the way out from the crisis by improving efficiency and productivity.   \par \par \uc2 Separately, advisory staff to the Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Muhammad Ikhsan argued the soaring international oil price would increase the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's oil and gas revenues. However, if the need for oil for electricity was included, the balance would be \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 As a result, he added, the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  would increase. Nevertheless, the situation was still considered secure since there might be under-\b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the 2007 Revised State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the remaining \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  could be used to compensate for the rising \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 According to Ikhsan, the critical area in the 2008 State \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was in the oil lifting volume target.   \par \par \uc2 "If the oil lifting volume is 1.034 million barrels and the international oil price is assumed at US$80-US$90 per barrel, the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  can reach IDR5 trillion-IDR6 trillion, which can still be compensated by IDR7 trillion in \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  fund. If the lifting oil volume cannot meet the target, we will be doomed," he inserted yesterday.   \par \par \uc2 He told that the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would increase if the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to the State Electricity Company (PLN) was included.   \par \par \uc2 "Every dollar increase in the oil price will increase the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to PLN by IDR600 billion." (Bisnis/gak/esu/bsi/luz)   \par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020071024e3ao00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
