 lot of investment, it also means that miners will need to deal more with the bureaucracy when it comes to processing permits," Priyo said.   \par \par \uc2 He said the IMA was pessimistic about the bill, saying it was unlikely the new \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  would create the foundation necessary to improve the investment climate in the mining sector.   \par \par \uc2 "We will see that there is still a lot of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially in determining the authority of the central government and local governments."   \par \par \uc2 The IMA also has warned the government against interfering with existing Contracts of Work (CoW), to show that it respects the sanctity of a contract.   \par \par \uc2 Under the bill, a transition period will be applied to CoW holders before they are gradually moved over to the new permit system introduced in the bill.   \par \par \uc2 The mining bill, which has been in discussions for more than a year, is expected to be enacted by the end of the year.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071030e3au00018\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
