\par\par \b \uc2 BI sees inflation risk in high oil prices   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 458 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 October 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has warned of another risk to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from surging global oil prices besides a possible increase in fuel-\b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , namely, a likely pick-up in inflation over the long run due to the rising cost of imported goods.   \par \par \uc2 The business community has also acknowledged the risk, and requested some slack in terms of the prices, and \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  imposed on, unsubsidized fuels to help keep increases in production costs -- and overall inflation -- to a minimum.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  senior deputy governor Miranda S. Goeltom said that though Indonesia could set off a possible increase in fuel-\b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  through higher exports of its commodities, such as coal and palm oil -- the demand and prices for which have also been rising -- such a situation would be unsustainable in the long term.   \par \par \uc2 "In the short run, Indonesia could gain through higher revenues, trade account surpluses and foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , despite a rise in \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Miranda said Tuesday during an event discussing the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook.   \par \par \uc2 "However, the second-stage effects might not be so favorable. This is because Indonesia still imports many goods as well, including those produced from the commodities."   \par \par \uc2 If the prices of raw materials and alternative fuels for production, as well as the end-products themselves, rose, then consumer prices would also be affected.   \par \par \uc2 As a result, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could in the long run come under more pressure from "imported inflation", which would eventually have an impact on BI's monetary policies.   \par \par \uc2 "So, I think we have to be cautious. We're confident that next year's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be better and inflation lower, but caution must still be exercised due to the many \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  arising from external factors," Miranda said, adding that BI was still standing by its forecast for inflation of between 5 and 7 percent this year.   \par \par \uc2 BI Governor Burhanuddin Abdullah had previously said that the recent strengthening of the rupiah could act to help counterbalance a possible pick-up in "imported inflation".   \par \par \uc2 However, the rupiah weakened to Rp 9,110 against the U.S. dollar Tuesday, while crude oil prices eased slightly to $92 a barrel in New York and $89 in London.   \par \par \uc2 In light of the current situation, Indonesian Association of Food and Beverage Producers (GAPMMI) chairman Thomas Dharmawan has asked that the possible risks of increased imported inflation be shouldered together, and not just left to producers.   \par \par \uc2 "If possible, the government should cut the \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  on unsubsidized fuels for commercial use, and not increase their prices," he said.   \par \par \uc2 "It would also be helpful in keeping production costs down by ensuring sufficient energy supplies for the domestic market, and not exporting them all just for windfall revenues."   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071031e3av00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
