\par\par \b \uc2 Unemployment still high despite good results   \b0\par\par\uc2 537 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 December 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 This year's results indicate that the government has been able lay down more solid foundations on which the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can grow further. But, for many people, this achievement will not be enough.   \par \par \uc2 Some politicians and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  observers say that the government has failed to solve the growing unemployment and poverty problem.   \par \par \uc2 Siswono Yudohasodo, the chairman of the Indonesian Farmers' Association (HKTI), for example, said the number of unemployed and poor people had not changed much since President Bambang Susilo Yudhoyono and Vice President M. Jusuf Kalla took power four years ago.   \par \par \uc2 Although the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has improved during the last four years, the number of people living under the poverty line remains high at between 34 million and 50 million, said Siswono, the running mate of presidential candidate Amien Rais, who ran against the Susilo-Kalla ticket in the 2004 presidential election.   \par \par \uc2 Siswono said that the number of openly unemployed also remained high at 10.6 million, or 9.8 percent of the total population as of June this year. This figure, according to Siswono, is relatively unchanged from 10.9 million, or 10.3 percent in 2005.   \par \par \uc2 The government has, in fact, introduced a number of programs to cope with the unemployment and poverty problems. The last measure was issued in June as a part of an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  package to stimulate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth by such things as improving the investment climate, speeding up infrastructural development and strengthening small and medium enterprises.   \par \par \uc2 With the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  packages, the government hopes that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will reach 6.3 percent this year and 6.9 percent in 2008, and that the unemployment rate will be reduced to between 8 percent and 9 percent next year.   \par \par \uc2 According to the government, the open unemployment rate dropped to 9.7 percent (10.5 million) in early 2007 from 10.44 percent (11.1 million) at the of 2006.   \par \par \uc2 With the improvement in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and the decline in the unemployment rate, the government is optimistic that the number of poor people will be reduced from 17.75 percent in 2006 to between 15 percent and 16.8 percent in 2008.   \par \par \uc2 In order to achieve this target, the government also plans to divert up to Rp 30 trillion (about US$3.3 billion) in routine \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  from the 2008 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to capital \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 This higher \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on infrastructure is expected to help create more jobs, which in turn will provide higher earnings for the poor.   \par \par \uc2 Unfortunately, the much-waited \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  packages could not be implemented due to the lack of technical guidance on how the government agencies involved should carry out the programs.   \par \par \uc2 With the improvements in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, the government has laid important foundations for creating faster and more solid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the coming years.   \par \par \uc2 However, to be able to do this, the government will need to place more focus on the implementation of its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and remove the legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in many \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fields.   \par \par \uc2 It will not be easy, but if the government can do it, regaining the high \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth rates with low inflation we enjoyed prior to the financial crisis in late 1997 will no longer be out of reach. - Hendarsyah Tarmizi   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071227e3cr00013\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
