\par\par \b \uc2 The law cannot be expected to enforce itself: Legislator   \b0\par\par\uc2 In 2007 law enforcement has failed to ensure security as well as resolve major cases from the past.   Azis Syamsuddin  , a criminal law expert and deputy chairman of the law commission at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  talked to  The Jakarta Post 's   Ridwan Max Sijabat   on this issue recently.   \par \uc2 844 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 December 2007\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 9\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2007 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Question: How do you evaluate law enforcement in 2007?   \par \par \uc2 Answer: I would like to tell President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono that, as in previous years, there was no rule of law this year (2007). We have government, but it has failed to enforce the law at all levels in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  life.   \par \par \uc2 Why do you say that?   \par \par \uc2 The law can't enforce itself, it must be enforced by the government. The President as the head of the government wasn't able to ensure Police and the Attorney General enforced the law, thus leaving us with legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 We see the President and law enforcers do not take actions against groups who use violence against the Ahmadiyah sect and other religious groups who use their houses for worship.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sees the President hasn't brought former aides involved in corruption to justice and has no political commitment to create good governance or settle unresolved past human rights and major corruption cases.   \par \par \uc2 Everyone sees the government violating the 1945 Constitution, which requires it to allocate 20 percent of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for education, but no move is made.   \par \par \uc2 People know that the President knows that the Police and Attorney General's Office are nests of corruption, but he doesn't do anything. He also knows the court has issued controversial verdicts going beyond a sense of fairness.   \par \par \uc2 The police see school-age children smoking and selling cigarettes in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  places, but no action is taken. The law is often broken in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  but now one does anything.   \par \par \uc2 All this means the government is committing a serious legal violation by way of omission.   \par \par \uc2 Why is the law unenforceable?   \par \par \uc2 The President and law enforcers do not set a good example. The people will follow suit if \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  figures keep the law. Law enforcers are not sufficiently aware of the importance of ensuring security, maintaining the political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability and achieving advances in all fields. Indonesia will not see significant progress unless a guarantee is given to ensure pluralism, protect hard work, prevent the use of violence and punish those violating the law.   \par \par \uc2 What major unresolved cases does the government have before it?   \par \par \uc2 Too many, in human rights, corruption and banking. If the government is committed to legal certainty it should immediately follow up on unresolved human rights cases in Jakarta, Nanggroe Aceh Darussalam, Papua and Central Sulawesi. It has to confront the alleged corruption of former president Soeharto and also former \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials and conglomerates known as the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Liquidity Support (BLBI) scandal.   \par \par \uc2 Why hasn't the House used its supervisory powers to press the government to settle the major cases?   \par \par \uc2 The House is not only home to numerous political factions but also many political brokers. Many legislators, it is believed, sit in the parliament to make money and to fight for partisan interests which aren't those of the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The House has also been shaken by several humiliating scandals this year, including the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  and arms procurement scams being investigated by the House ethics body.   \par \par \uc2 The executive has frequently ignored recommendations made after House inquiries, because factions and legislators are fighting their own political battles instead of doing their job, which is to channel the people's interests and aspirations.   \par \par \uc2 What is your comment on the performance of the House's law commission in enforcing the laws?   \par \par \uc2 The law commission has the Police, the Anticorruption Commission, the AGO and the Supreme Court as its working partners. But we have talked too much and the authority to enforce the law is in the hands of the President and law enforcers. We don't need talk but rather an unbiased law enforcement effort that isn't biased on the basis of position, status and education.   \par \par \uc2 Why do you frequently go beyond your faction's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the House?   \par \par \uc2 I am representing the people and my constituents more than my party. I am paid not by the party but by the people through the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Therefore, the party's policies shouldn't contravene the people's interests.   \par \par \uc2 I do not fear being recalled at any time if I am considered too outspoken. I have a lot of work to do for people outside the parliament. But my party (Golkar Party) has been more democratic in such cases with the emergence of young leaders in the party and the parliament.   \par \par \uc2 Why have you made the meetings of the commission's illegal logging working committee open to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ?   \par \par \uc2 As chairman of the working committee I have no reason to keep the meeting closed to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Illegal logging is a high-profile issue and the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  has a right to know why the government can't stop it.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020071231e3cv00013\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
