\par\par \b \uc2 A managed floating forex system better for RI: Economist   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 424 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 January 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI), is better off using a managed floating exchange rate regime than a freely floating one to help control the rupiah against the U.S. dollar, an economist said.   \par \par \uc2 The monetary authority has revised its forex system three times since 1970. A fixed forex system in place between 1970-1978 was followed by managed floating between 1978-1997 and then free floating since August 1997.   \par \par \uc2 However, in defense of a doctoral dissertation Wednesday Erna Zetha Rahman of University of Indonesia (UI) said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  needed to revert back to the managed floating system in place before August 1997.   \par \par \uc2 "A managed floating regime makes the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grow, as it allows the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to supervise the rupiah and ... according push on inflation rates," Erna Zetha told the forum.   \par \par \uc2 "A freely floating regime, meanwhile, makes the rupiah fluctuate, which affects the stability of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and may eventually hamper \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development," said Erna, who is also a member of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry's (Kadin) \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team.   \par \par \uc2 A managed floating forex system would see the introduction of a so-called intervention band to guide \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  market interventions and keep the rupiah within a desired range.   \par \par \uc2 Under a free-floating system meanwhile, no band exists to guide interventions.   \par \par \uc2 In 1997, when the crisis struck, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had to change its forex system as the rupiah depreciated to a level surpassing the upper limit of the intervention band.   \par \par \uc2 Erna expressed her opinion that a free-floating forex regime was risky and prone to social, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political turmoil, both external and internal.   \par \par \uc2 "The rupiah is becoming too easily influenced by market sentiments, creating \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  for investors in the production sector and eventually hindering \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth."   \par \par \uc2 However, Erna also said that while a de jure free-floating regime had been in place since August 1997 -- as mandated by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) -- the country has in fact had a managed-floating regime since the third quarter of 2002.   \par \par \uc2 According to Erna, since the silent adoption of the managed regime by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had improved year-by-year with relatively low inflation rates, except in 2005 when the government raised fuel prices.   \par \par \uc2 The country's inflation rate reached 17.11 percent in 2005 from 6.4 percent in the previous year. However, it dropped to 6.6 percent in 2006 and to 6.59 percent last year. (adt)   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080111e41b0001h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
