\par\par \b \uc2 Djoni Bustan: Biofuel maker facing constraints   \b0\par\par\uc2 Khairul Saleh , The Jakarta Post, Palembang, South Sumatra   \par \uc2 604 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 January 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 24\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 For one couple, four years of research and experiments have come to fruition, with very positive results.   \par \par \uc2 Djoni Bustan, who has a PhD in mechanical engineering, and his wife Sri Haryati, have created a number of different kinds of biofuels from crude palm oil (CPO), sugarcane residue, coal and castor seeds -- with coal and CPO-based fuel in the trial stage.   \par \par \uc2 Their series of experiments with CPO produced the general types of fuel needed like bio-gasoline, bio-kerosene and biodiesel, through three reactors, which are capable of converting triglycerides into a paraffin, olefin, naphtene and aromatic (PONA) compound.   \par \par \uc2 The quality of Djoni's biofuel is higher than market products (of state oil and gas firm Pertamina), with various advantages.   \par \par \uc2 The process of manufacturing biodiesel using renewable resources generally requires a single-step transesterification reaction.   \par \par \uc2 But the biofuel is not immediately ready for use.   \par \par \uc2 Djoni's biodiesel is ready for use, with physical properties resembling those of Pertamina's diesel oil, because his machines can change CPO into PONA.   \par \par \uc2 This biodiesel also has higher aromatic and octane numbers than Pertamina diesel.   \par \par \uc2 "Now we are only making improvements, such as in combustion stability, through our demo plant," Djoni said.   \par \par \uc2 "Combustion trials have shown that our fuel burns faster than market products."   \par \par \uc2 Previous laboratory tests and the current pilot plant experiments have shown his biofuel is a promising but costly alternative fuel.   \par \par \uc2 The completion of this demo-plant phase will take a maximum period of six months and require more funds.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  side of this innovation can be ascertained only after the present demo stage, with mass production to follow.   \par \par \uc2 "The problem is that the local CPO price is unstable. The government should aim to bring down the price of renewable energy," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Djoni is chairman of the South Sumatra Council of Experts and said he was optimistic once biofuel is widely marketed, it will buffer the fuel supply and the nation will be independent in the field of energy.   \par \par \uc2 He said biofuel should be produced in rural areas, where the raw materials are produced, before being delivered to cities. Though investors are interested in biofuel production, the unstable price of CPO has prompted most of them to cancel or postpone their plans.   \par \par \uc2 Djoni said if the central government and the oil palm business association could not control the price of CPO, any attempt to manufacture biofuel from CPO would be futile, because of its uncompetitive price.   \par \par \uc2 Gasoline is now priced at Rp 4,500 per liter compared to Rp 7,000 for CPO.   \par \par \uc2 "With the CPO price \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  today, investors' CPO-based fuel production schemes will not materialize," he said.   \par \par \uc2 While anticipating favorable policies, Djoni said he hoped the South Sumatra provincial administration would issue a regional bylaw requiring oil palm estate companies to build biofuel plants on their plantations.   \par \par \uc2 "It would be an unusual \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but the central government in fact has not made such a rule yet," he said.   \par \par \uc2 The couple continues to conduct trials and explore the possibility of cooperation with estates.   \par \par \uc2 In Djoni's view, estate firms will suffer no losses with the presence of biofuel plants because their estates and CPO-based fuel processing units are integrated.   \par \par \uc2 "Ideally, the plants become one with the estate environment so that plantation waste can be utilized and the distribution of fuel products will meet the demand of local people as well.   \par \par \uc2 "If this happens, villages will likely develop into centers of energy sources," Djoni said.   \par \par \uc2 He said he is registering his novel products for intellectual property rights.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080122e41m0001a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
