\par\par \b \uc2 Govt prepares in anticipation of U.S. recession   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 463 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 January 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Against the backdrop of a possible U.S. recession, which has sent stock markets across the globe tumbling, the government is preparing measures to safeguard the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability.   \par \par \uc2 "With this situation, the indicators in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and stability have changed drastically.   \par \par \uc2 "Furthermore, we can almost be sure that there will be a U.S. recession as we see the ongoing prospects," Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Boediono said after a meeting with other top government officials.   \par \par \uc2 Analysts have predicted that the United States, the largest \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  power in the world, may suffer a recession triggered by housing and credit woes that would hurt the country's demand for imports.   \par \par \uc2 "We will safeguard the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  anchor to anticipate this situation," Boediono said.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah fell to Rp 9,475 against the U.S. dollar from Rp 9,460 the previous day. Meanwhile, the Jakarta Composite Index fell the most in five years by 7.7 percent to close at 2,294.52, following falls in other markets in the world.   \par \par \uc2 Other Asian countries' stock markets also suffered a decline. The stock index in Hong Kong dropped 8.7 percent, South Korea 4.4 percent, Shanghai 7 percent, Tokyo 5.7 percent and India 6.12 percent, after it was shut down temporarily.   \par \par \uc2 "At present, the world's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is facing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said Boediono.   \par \par \uc2 "However, if we can maintain our efforts to develop infrastructure projects and improve the country's investment climate, I believe our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will remain resilient."   \par \par \uc2 The government, he said, would focus on developing infrastructure and stabilizing the prices of staple foodstuffs at home to help keep the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  growing.   \par \par \uc2 Infrastructure development is an essential factor for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth as it helps to reduce costs, while surging prices of staple foods will affect the inflation rate and eventually people's purchasing power.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono was however upbeat that Indonesia would only be slightly affected by the U.S. recession as the price of the country's top commodities, including those from the energy, agriculture and mining sectors, kept increasing due to high global demand.   \par \par \uc2 Similar optimism is also shared by Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati, who said that the government would maintain the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 1.7 percent of the gross domestic product, or Rp 74 trillion.   \par \par \uc2 "The government will seek more revenue from the oil and gas sector, commodity exports and state-owned enterprise profits, as well as \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incomes, to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she said.   \par \par \uc2 Mulyani said the government this year had also allocated Rp 75.5 trillion to subsidize the energy sector and Rp 22.2 trillion to other sectors. (adt)   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080123e41n00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal44